==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Antechoir
<hw>An"te*choir`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A space inclosed or reserved at the entrance to the
choir, for the clergy and choristers.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Where a
choir is divided, as in some Spanish churches, that division of it which
is the farther from the sanctuary.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Antecians</ent>⟦br⟧
